    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNo way to **structurally** restrict the scope of searching (and replacing/acting) with `:s` and friends.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAllow scoping `:s` and `:g` with treesitter captures, e.g.,\n```vim\n:s/foo/bar/@comment\n```\nto only search and replace inside comment captures. Should respect the usual fallback (e.g., also replace in `@comment.documentation`). \n\nStretch goal: search _outside_ a capture with `:s/.../.../!@comment`.\n\nSee https://github.com/vigoux/architext.nvim (which allows specifying arbitrary tree-sitter queries, but highlight captures seem like a sweet spot for power vs. usability).\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
